#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid "Objective:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:66
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Hit the ball into the hole (gray circle) to move on the next."
msgid "Put the ball into the hole with the least possible hits."
msgstr "Slå bolden i hullet (den grå cirkel) for at gå videre til det næste."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:68
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "&kolf;'s game-play is simple. It is easiest to learn how to play hands-"
#| "on, and thus a tutorial course is included to guide you through the "
#| "basics. This chapter will guide you through this tutorial. To start the "
#| "tutorial, choose <menuchoice><guimenu>Help</"
#| "guimenu><guimenuitem>Tutorial</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgid ""
"&kolf;'s game-play is simple. It is the easiest to learn how to play hands-"
"on, and thus a tutorial course is included to guide you through the basics. "
"This chapter will guide you through this tutorial. To start the tutorial, "
"choose the <menuchoice><guimenu>Help</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Tutorial</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item."
msgstr ""
"Spil af &kolf; er nemt nok. Det er nemmest at lære det ved at gøre det, så "
"derfor er en øvelsesbane inkluderet til at vejlede dig gennem det basale. "
"Dette kapitel vil lede dig gennem denne øvelse. For at starte øvelsen, "
"vælges <menuchoice><guimenu>Hjælp</guimenu><guimenuitem>Gennemgang</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid "Hitting the Ball"
msgstr "At slå til bolden"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:72
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "To aim the ball, either line up the mouse behind the ball so the putter "
#| "aims in the direction you want to hit it or press one of the <keycap>Left "
#| "Arrow</keycap> (counterclockwise) or <keycap>Right Arrow</keycap> "
#| "(clockwise) keys, to rotate the putter."
msgid ""
"To aim the ball, either line up the mouse behind the ball so the putter aims "
"in the direction you want to hit it or press one of the &Left; arrow "
"(counterclockwise) or &Right; arrow (clockwise) keys, to rotate the putter."
msgstr ""
"For at sigte med bolden, skal musen enten være bagved bolden så putteren "
"sigter i den retning du ønsker, eller en af tasterne <keycap>Venstre pil</"
"keycap> (mod uret) eller <keycap>Højre pil</keycap> (med uret) skal trykkes "
"på og holdes nede, for at rotere putteren."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:76
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "To rotate the putter more quickly with the keyboard, hold down "
#| "<keycap>Shift</keycap> while pressing or holding the arrow keys. To "
#| "rotate more slowly, hold down <keycap>Control</keycap>."
msgid ""
"To rotate the putter more quickly with the keyboard, hold down &Shift; while "
"pressing or holding the arrow keys. To rotate more slowly, hold down &Ctrl;."
msgstr ""
"For at rotere putteren hurtigere med tastaturet, holdes <keycap>Shift</"
"keycap> mens der trykkes på piletasterne. For at rotere langsommere, holdes "
"<keycap>Control</keycap> nede"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:78
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "To hit the ball, press and hold either the &LMB; or <keycap>Down Arrow</"
#| "keycap> key. The longer you hold down the key or button, the more "
#| "strength the putt will have. It will take practice to get a good feel for "
#| "speed."
msgid ""
"To hit the ball, press and hold either the &LMB; or &Down; arrow key. The "
"longer you hold down the key or button, the more strength the putt will "
"have. It will take practice to get a good feel for speed."
msgstr ""
"For at slå bolden, tryk  på venstre museknap og hold den nede, eller "
"<keycap>nedad-pilen</keycap> kan bruges. Jo længere du trykker på knappen "
"eller tasten, desto mere kraft får puttet. Det kræves øvelse at få en god "
"fornemmelse for hastigheden."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:83
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "To stop abort the putt while you are still holding moving the putter back "
#| "in your stroke, press <keycap>Escape</keycap>."
msgid ""
"To stop the putt while you are still holding moving the putter back in your "
"stroke, press &Esc;."
msgstr ""
"For at afbryde putten mens du stadigvæk holder putteren tilbage i slaget, "
"tryk på <keycap>Esc</keycap>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:86
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Hit the ball into the hole (gray circle) to move on the next."
msgid "Hit the ball into the hole to move on to the next."
msgstr "Slå bolden i hullet (den grå cirkel) for at gå videre til det næste."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:90 index.docbook:682
#, no-c-format
msgid "Slopes"
msgstr "Hældninger"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:91
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Slopes are areas of slanted down that the golf ball rolls down in an "
#| "expected manner. The light of the golf course is from the upper-left, so "
#| "the brightest slopes will push the ball towards the upper-left corner of "
#| "the hole. Choose <menuchoice><guimenu>Hole</guimenu><guimenuitem>Show "
#| "Info</guimenuitem></menuchoice> to see an arrow that points in the "
#| "direction the slope will roll the ball."
msgid ""
"Slopes are slanted areas of the course that the golf ball rolls down in an "
"expected manner. The light of the golf course is from the upper-left, so the "
"brightest slopes will push the ball towards the upper-left corner of the "
"hole. Choose the <menuchoice><guimenu>Hole</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Show Info</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item to see an arrow that points in the "
"direction the slope will roll the ball."
msgstr ""
"Hældninger er områder som golfbolden ruller nedad på en uventet måde. Lyset "
"falder oppefra til venstre på golfbanen, så den lyseste hældning vil få "
"bolden til at rulle mod hullet i det øverste venstre hjørne. Vælg "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Hul</guimenu><guimenuitem>Vis information</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> for at se en pil som peger i den retning som "
"hældningen vil få bolden til at rulle."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:92
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On this tutorial hole, hit the ball onto the upward-pointing slope and let "
"it roll into the cup to move onto the next hole."
msgstr ""
"For øvelseshullet, slå bolden på den opadpegende hældning og lad den rulle "
"ned i hullet for at komme videre til næste hul."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:95
#, no-c-format
msgid "Directions"
msgstr "Retninger"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:96
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "On the next hole, experiment with the other kinds of slopes. There are "
#| "elliptical, vertical, horizontal, and diagonal slopes in &kolf;. Hit the "
#| "ball into the hole."
msgid ""
"On the next hole, experiment with the other kinds of slopes. There are "
"elliptical, vertical, horizontal, and diagonal slopes in &kolf;. Hit the "
"ball into the hole."
msgstr ""
"Eksperimentér med andre slags hældninger på næste hul. Der findes runde, "
"lodrette, vandrette og diagonale hældninger i &kolf;. Slå bolden i hullet."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:98
#, no-c-format
msgid "Steepness"
msgstr "Stejlhed"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:99
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The next tutorial hole has two slopes of differing steepness. If you "
#| "choose <menuchoice><guimenu>Hole</guimenu><guimenuitem>Show Info</"
#| "guimenuitem></menuchoice>, the steepness of the slope will appear as a "
#| "number from 1-8, where 8 is steepest and 1 is shallowest. Also, the more "
#| "extreme shading the slope has, the steeper it is. Hit the ball into the "
#| "hole and continue to the next hole."
msgid ""
"The next tutorial hole has two slopes of differing steepness. If you choose "
"the <menuchoice><guimenu>Hole</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Show Info</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item, the steepness of the slope will appear "
"as a number from 1-8, where 8 is steepest and 1 is shallowest. Hit the ball "
"into the hole and continue to the next hole."
msgstr ""
"Næste øvelseshul har to hældninger med forskellig stejlhed. Hvis du vælger "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Hul</guimenu><guimenuitem>Vis information</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>, så ses hældningens stejlhed som et tal mellem 1 "
"og 8, hvor 8 er stejlest og 1 er mindst stejl. Desuden, jo kraftigere skygge "
"hældningen har, desto stejlere er den. Slå i bolden i hullet og fortsæt med "
"næste hul."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:103
#, no-c-format
msgid "Walls"
msgstr "Vægge"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Balls bounce of walls as one would expect them to, with a little bit of "
"dampening. Deflect the ball off the walls and into the cup to advance to the "
"next hole."
msgstr ""
"Bolde støder mod væggene som man skulle forvente sig at de gør, men en vis "
"dæmpning. Stød bolden via væggen ned i hullet for at gå videre til næste hul."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:107 index.docbook:711
#, no-c-format
msgid "Puddles and Sand"
msgstr "Vandpytter og sandbunker"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:108
#, no-c-format
msgid "Puddles"
msgstr "Vandpytter"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:109
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Puddles are blue. When your ball rolls into a puddle, a penalty stroke is "
#| "added to your score and your ball is placed outside the puddle."
msgid ""
"Puddles are blue. When your ball rolls into a puddle, a penalty stroke is "
"added to your score and you must then choose where you want to take your "
"next shot from: either next to the puddle or from the same place as where "
"you just took the last shot."
msgstr ""
"Vandpytter er blå. Når bolden ruller ned i vandet, så lægges et straffeslag "
"til i points, og bolden placeres udenfor vandet."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:111
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sand"
msgstr "Sand"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:112
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sand is yellow. Balls roll through sand very slowly."
msgstr "Sandbunker er gule. Bolde ruller meget langsomt gennem sandet."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:113
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Hit the ball around the puddles and through the sand into the hole to "
"continue to the next tutorial hole."
msgstr ""
"Slå bolden rundt om vandpytterne, og gennem sandet ned i hullet, og fortsæt "
"med næste øvelseshul."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:117 index.docbook:734
#, no-c-format
msgid "Windmills"
msgstr "Vindmøller"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:118
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Windmills are compound objects with brown border walls and a moving arm "
#| "at either the top or bottom of the object. Half-walls create the opening "
#| "to the windmill, which a black arm swings across. It takes practice to be "
#| "able to time stroke of the ball to pass through the opening. Hit the ball "
#| "through the windmill into the hole to continue."
msgid ""
"Windmills are compound objects with brown border walls and a moving arm on "
"one side. Half-walls create the opening to the windmill, which the black arm "
"swings across. It takes practice to be able to time the stroke of the ball "
"to pass through the opening. Hit the ball through the windmill into the hole "
"to continue."
msgstr ""
"Vindmøller er sammensatte objekter, med brune kantvægge og en bevægelig "
"vinge enten ved toppen eller bunden. Halvvægge danner åbningen til "
"vejrmøllen, hvor en sort vinge svinger forbi. Det kræver øvelse at kunne slå "
"bolden på det rette tidspunkt for at komme gennem åbningen. Slå bolden ved "
"vindmøllen ned i hullet for at fortsætte."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:121
#, no-c-format
msgid "Black Holes"
msgstr "Sort hul"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:122
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "When you hit your ball into a black hole, it is transported to the exit "
#| "and ejected at the angle of the exit at a speed directly relational to "
#| "the speed your ball was going. Choose <menuchoice><guimenu>Hole</"
#| "guimenu><guimenuitem>Show Info</guimenuitem></menuchoice> to see which "
#| "Black Hole goes to which exit and which direction the ball will come out "
#| "of the exit. The rim around Black Holes and their corresponding exits are "
#| "also the same color. Hit the ball into the black hole, which will then "
#| "eject the ball into the cup so you can go to the next hole."
msgid ""
"When you hit your ball into a black hole, it is transported to the exit and "
"ejected at the angle of the exit at a speed directly relational to the speed "
"your ball was going. Choose the <menuchoice><guimenu>Hole</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Show Info</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item to see which "
"Black Hole goes to which exit and which direction the ball will come out of "
"the exit. The rim around Black Holes are the same color as their "
"corresponding exits. Hit the ball into the black hole, which will then eject "
"the ball into the cup so you can go to the next hole."
msgstr ""
"Når du slår bolden ind i et sort hul, transporteres den til udgangen og "
"sendes ud med en udgangsvinkel, og en hastighed som er direkte proportionel "
"med hastigheden som bolden havde. Vælg <menuchoice><guimenu>Hul</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Vis information</guimenuitem></menuchoice> for at se "
"hvilket sort hul går til hvilken udgang, og hvilken retning bolden kommer ud "
"med. Kanten rundt om sorte huller og tilsvarende udgange har også samme "
"farve. Slå bolden ind i det sorte hul, som så sender bolden ned i hullet, så "
"du kan gå til næste hul."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:125 index.docbook:749
#, no-c-format
msgid "Floaters"
msgstr "Flydere"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:126
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Floaters are moving platforms that carry a ball that lands on it. Floaters' "
"speeds vary. This one is a pretty slow floater, but you still must time your "
"shot so you can go over the wall and into the cup."
msgstr ""
"Flydere er bevægelige platforme, som lader en bold der lander på dem flyde. "
"Flydernes hastighed varierer. Denne er en ganske langsom en, men du skal "
"stadigvæk slå på det rigtige tidspunkt, så du kommer over væggen og ned i "
"hullet."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:129
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bridges"
msgstr "Broer"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Bridges are simple - they just lift the ball above the things below them, "
"like slopes, sand, and puddles. They can have brown walls on their perimeter."
msgstr ""
"Broer er enkle: de løfter kun bolden over ting under dem, såsom hældninger, "
"sandbunker og vandpytter. De kan have brune vægge langs kanterne."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:134
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game Rules, Strategies and Tips"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:136
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Here's in-depth description of &kolf;'s basic features."
msgid "Here's in-depth description of &kolf;'s basic features."
msgstr "Her er en indgående beskrivelse af &kolf;s grundlæggende funktioner."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:139
#, no-c-format
msgid "Starting a Game"
msgstr "Start et spil"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:141
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "To start a game, choose <menuchoice><guimenu>Game</"
#| "guimenu><guimenuitem>New</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. This opens a dialog "
#| "where you can configure your new game."
msgid ""
"To start a game, choose the <menuchoice><guimenu>Game</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>New</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item. This opens a dialog "
"where you can configure your new game."
msgstr ""
"For at starte en omgang, vælges <menuchoice><guimenu>Spil</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Ny</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Dette åbner en dialog "
"hvor du kan indstille den nye omgang."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:151
#, no-c-format
msgid "Players Page"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:152
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To add a player to your game, click the <guibutton>New Player</guibutton> "
"button."
msgstr ""
"For at tilføje en spiller til spillet, klikkes på knappen <guibutton>Ny "
"spiller</guibutton>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:155
#, no-c-format
msgid "To change the name of the players, change the text in the text boxes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:162
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To remove a player, click the <guibutton>Remove</guibutton> button next to "
"the player's name."
msgstr ""
"For at fjerne en spiller, klikkes på knappen <guibutton>Fjern</guibutton> "
"ved siden af spillerens navn."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:167
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Course name:"
