msgid ""
"Switch to the edit mode using the <menuchoice><guimenu>Hole</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Edit</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item. Choose the "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Hole</guimenu> <guimenuitem>New</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> menu item to add a new hole at the end of the course."
msgstr ""
"Vælg <menuchoice><guimenu>Hul</guimenu><guimenuitem>Ny</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> for at tilføje et nyt hul sidst i banen."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:616
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "You can restore a hole to a blank state, similar to when it was first "
#| "created, by choosing <menuchoice><guimenu>Hole</"
#| "guimenu><guimenuitem>Clear</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgid ""
"You can restore a hole to a blank state, similar to when it was first "
"created, by choosing the <menuchoice><guimenu>Hole</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Clear</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item."
msgstr ""
"Du kan nulstille et hul til den tomme tilstand, som ligner den da hullet "
"først oprettedes, ved at vælge <menuchoice><guimenu>Hul</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Ryd</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:618
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Two items will appear on new holes: a cup, and a white ball. The white ball "
"marks where players' balls start the hole."
msgstr ""
"To objekter ses for nye hul, en kop og en hvid bold. Den hvide bold markerer "
"hvor spillernes bolde starter hullet."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:621
#, no-c-format
msgid "Editing Basics"
msgstr "Grundlæggende redigering"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:622
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The basic building block of &kolf; courses is the <quote>object</quote>. "
#| "Holes are made up of a bunch of objects. Objects can be moved to any "
#| "location, and the different kinds of objects each have different "
#| "properties you can set."
msgid ""
"The basic building block of &kolf; courses is the <quote>object</quote>. "
"Holes are made up of a bunch of objects. Objects can be moved to any "
"location, and the different kinds of objects each have different properties "
"you can set."
msgstr ""
"Den grundlæggende byggeblok for &kolf;s baner er <quote>objektet</quote>. "
"Huller består af et antal objekter. Objekter kan flyttes til hvilken plads "
"som helst, og de forskellige objekter har alle forskellige egenskaber som du "
"kan indstille."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:623
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "To start editing a hole, toggle the <menuchoice><guimenu>Hole</"
#| "guimenu><guimenuitem>Edit</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item, or press "
#| "the pencil icon on the toolbar. To leave editing mode, uncheck this menu "
#| "item (or the toolbar icon)."
msgid ""
"To start editing a hole, toggle the <menuchoice><guimenu>Hole</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Edit</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item, or press the pencil "
"icon on the toolbar. To leave editing mode, uncheck this menu item (or the "
"toolbar icon)."
msgstr ""
"For at begynde at redigere et hul, markeres menupunktet "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Hul</guimenu><guimenuitem>Redigér</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>, eller der trykkes på penslen i værktøjslinjen. For at forlade "
"redigeringstilstand, afmarkeres menupunktet (eller ikonen i værktøjslinjen)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:625
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding Objects"
msgstr "Tilføj objekter"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:626
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To add a new object to the course, choose its name in the list box labeled "
"<guilabel>Add object:</guilabel>. The object will appear in the center of "
"the course."
msgstr ""
"For at tilføje et nyt objekt til banen, vælges navnet i listefeltet som "
"hedder <guilabel>Tilføj objekt:</guilabel>. Objektet vises i midten af banen."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:628
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Bridges and signs will cover up new objects if they were already in the "
"center of the hole."
msgstr ""
"Broer og skilte dækker nye objekter hvis de allerede fandtes på banens midte."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:639
#, no-c-format
msgid "Moving and Resizing Objects"
msgstr "Flyt og ændr størrelse på objekter"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:640
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Move your mouse cursor over the object that you want to move, and the mouse "
"cursor will change to a hand cursor. Then click and drag the object to where "
"you want it."
msgstr ""
"Flyt musemarkøren til objektet som du vil flytte, så ændres markøren til en "
"hånd. Klik derefter og træk objektet derhen hvor du vil have det."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:641
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Puddles, sand, floaters, bridges, and signs can be resized by dragging the "
"small circle at their lower-right corner."
msgstr ""
"Størrelsen på vandpytter, sandbunker, flydere, broer og skilte kan ændres "
"ved at trække i den lille cirkel i nederste højre hjørne."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:644
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Walls can be moved by clicking and dragging their endpoints, or you can move "
"the whole wall by clicking and dragging on the middle part of the wall as "
"normal."
msgstr ""
"Vægge kan flyttes ved at klikke og trække i deres endepunkter, eller også "
"kan hele væggen flyttes ved at klikke og trække i væggens midte som normalt."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:648
#, no-c-format
msgid "Objects' Settings"
msgstr "Indstillinger for objekter"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:649
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Objects' properties can be changed in the area at the lower-right corner "
#| "of the &kolf; window. To edit an object, move your mouse cursor over it "
#| "until the cursor changes to the hand cursor. Then click. Various controls "
#| "for that object will appear in the lower-right corner of the &kolf; "
#| "window."
msgid ""
"Objects' properties can be changed in the area at the lower-right corner of "
"the &kolf; window. To edit an object, move your mouse cursor over it until "
"the cursor changes to the hand cursor. Then click. Various controls for that "
"object will appear in the lower-right corner of the &kolf; window."
msgstr ""
"Objekternes egenskaber kan ændres fra området i nederste højre hjørne af "
"&kolf;s vindue. For at redigere et objekt, flyttes musen over det til "
"markøren ændres til en hånd. Klik så. Forskellige værdier for objektet vises "
"i nederste højre hjørne i &kolf;s vindue."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:650
#, no-c-format
msgid "General Hole Settings"
msgstr "Generelle indstillinger for et hul"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:651
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To edit general hole settings, click an area of the hole that is not covered "
"by an object. When this is possible, the cursor will be the normal pointer "
"cursor."
msgstr ""
"For at redigere de generelle indstillinger for hullet, klikkes på et område "
"af hullet som ikke dækkes af et objekt. Når dette er muligt ser markøren ud "
"som den almindelige pil."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:654
#, no-c-format
msgid "Course name:"
msgstr "Banens navn:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:656
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "This is the name that is shown in the new game dialog and in the "
#| "<guimenuitem>About Course</guimenuitem> dialog."
msgid ""
"This is the name that is shown in the <guilabel>New Game</guilabel> dialog "
"and in the <guilabel>Course Information</guilabel> dialog."
msgstr ""
"Dette er navnet som vises i dialogen for nyt spil og i dialogen "
"<guimenuitem>Om banen</guimenuitem>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:659
#, no-c-format
msgid "Course author:"
msgstr "Banens forfatter:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:661
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "This is the author name that is shown in the <guimenuitem>About Course</"
#| "guimenuitem> dialog."
msgid ""
"This is the author name that is shown in the <guilabel>Course Information</"
"guilabel> dialog."
msgstr ""
"Dette er forfatterens navn som vises i dialogen <guimenuitem>Om bane</"
"guimenuitem>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:664
#, no-c-format
msgid "Par:"
msgstr "Par:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:666
#, no-c-format
msgid "The par of the hole."
msgstr "Hullets par."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:669
#, no-c-format
msgid "Maximum:"
msgstr "Maksimum:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:671
#, no-c-format
msgid "The maximum number of strokes a player can take on the hole."
msgstr "Maksimalt antal slag som en spiller må udføre for hullet."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:674
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show border walls"
msgstr "Vis vægkanter"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:676
#, no-c-format
msgid "Whether or not to show walls around the border of the hole."
msgstr "Om vægge skal vises eller ej omkring hullets kant."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:685
#, no-c-format
msgid "Type"
msgstr "Type"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:687
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choose the type of the slope - <guilabel>Vertical</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>Horizontal</guilabel>, <guilabel>Diagonal</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>Opposite Diagonal</guilabel>, <guilabel>Circular</guilabel>. "
"Diagonal and opposite diagonal slopes are triangles, while circular slopes "
"are circles. Vertical and horizontal slopes are rectangles of course."
msgstr ""
"Vælg hældningens type: <guilabel>Lodret</guilabel>, <guilabel>Vandret</"
"guilabel>, <guilabel>Diagonal</guilabel>, <guilabel>Motsat diagonal</"
"guilabel> eller <guilabel>Rund</guilabel>. Diagonale og modsat diagonale "
"hældninger er trekanter, mens runde hældninger er cirkler. Lodrette og "
"vandrette hældninger er naturligvis rektangulære."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:690
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reverse direction"
msgstr "Modsat retning"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:692
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whether or not to reverse the slant of the slope. For example, consider an "
"elliptical slope (a circular slope). When it is not reversed, it pushes "
"balls outward like a mound. When it is reversed, it sucks balls inward like "
"a hole."
msgstr ""
"Om hældningen skal have modsat retning eller ej. Tænk for eksempel over en "
"rund hældning (cirkulær hældning). Hvis den ikke er modsat, så ruller den "
"bolden udad som en bakke. Når den er modsat, så trækker den bolden til sig "
"som et hul."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:695
#, no-c-format
msgid "Unmovable"
msgstr "Kan ikke flyttes"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:697
#, no-c-format
msgid "Whether or not this can be moved by other objects, like floaters."
msgstr "Om dette kan flyttes af andre objekter, såsom flydere, eller ej."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:699
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If a floater overlaps with this object at any point on this path, and the "
#| "slope is large and thus won't move the floater, you <emphasis>must</"
#| "emphasis> make the slope <guilabel>Unmovable</guilabel>, or &kolf; will "
#| "suffer poor performance!"
msgid ""
"If a floater overlaps with this object at any point on this path, and the "
"slope is large and thus won't move the floater, you <emphasis>must</"
"emphasis> make the slope <guilabel>Unmovable</guilabel>, or &kolf; will "
"suffer poor performance!"
msgstr ""
"Hvis en flyder overlapper dette objekt på noget sted sin vej, og hældningen "
"er stor, og derfor ikke flytter flyderen, <emphasis>skal</emphasis> du gøre "
"hældningen <guilabel>Uflyttelig</guilabel>, ellers bliver &kolf;s ydelse "
"dårlig."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:703
#, no-c-format
msgid "Grade:"
msgstr "Niveau:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:705
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choose the grade (steepness) of the slope by moving the slider so the grade "
"moves towards 0 or 8, where 8 is steepest and 0 is flat. Steeper slopes push "
"the ball more."
msgstr ""
"Vælg niveauet (stejlheden) for hældningen ved at flytte skyderen så niveauet "
"går mod 0 eller 8, hvor 8 is stejlest og 0 is fladt. Stejlere hældninger "
"skubber mere til bolden."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:712
#, no-c-format
msgid "Puddles and Sand have the same configuration options as each other."
msgstr "Vandpytter og sandbunker har de samme indstillingsmuligheder."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:715
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enable show/hide"
msgstr "Aktivér Gem/Skjul"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:717
#, no-c-format
msgid "Checking this enables the flashing of this puddle or sand."
msgstr ""
"Markeres dette så aktiveres blinkning for vandpytterne eller sandbunkerne."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:724
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The more towards <guilabel>Fast</guilabel> the slider is, the faster the "
"puddle or sand flashes."
msgstr ""
"Jo længere mod <guilabel>Hurtig</guilabel> skyderen flyttes, desto hurtigere "
"blinker vandpytten eller sandbunken."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:730
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bridges, Windmills, Floaters, and Signs"
msgstr "Broer, vejrmøller, flydere og skilte"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:731
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Bridges, windmills, floaters, and signs all have similar settings for "
"configuring on which sides there are border walls. To show the wall on a "
"side, check the check box for that side."
msgstr ""
"Broer, vejrmøller, flyder og skilter har alle lignende opsætning for at "
"indstille på hvilke sider der er kantvægge. For at vise væggen langs en "
"side, markeres afkrydsningsfeltet for denne side."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:732
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are also some more specific options for windmills, floaters, and signs."
msgstr "Der er også nogle specielle tilvalg for vejrmøller, flydere og skilte."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:736
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Windmill on bottom"
msgid "Windmill on top"
msgstr "Vindmølle for neden"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:738
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Whether or not the black windmill arm is on bottom or top - the default "
#| "is that it is on the bottom. The two half-walls will always be with the "
#| "arm. Note that you cannot enable a border wall on the side that the arm "
#| "is."
msgid ""
"Whether or not the black windmill arm is on bottom or top - the default is "
"that it is on the top. The two half-walls will always be with the arm. Note "
"that you cannot enable a border wall on the side that the arm is."
msgstr ""
"Om den sorte vejrmøllevinge er længst nede eller længst oppe. Normalt er den "
"længst nede. De to halvvægge hører altid sammen med vingen. Bemærk at du "
"ikke kan aktivere en kantvæg på den side hvor vingen findes."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:741
#, no-c-format
msgid "Speed"
msgstr "Hastighed"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:743
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The more towards <guilabel>Fast</guilabel> the slider is, the faster the "
"black windmill arm moves."
msgstr ""
"Jo længere mod <guilabel>Hurtig</guilabel> skyderen flyttes, desto hurtigere "
"bevæges vejrmøllens vinge."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:750
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The path the floater moves along is shown by the wall it's connected to."
msgstr ""
"Vejen som flyderen flytter sig langs, vises af væggen som den hører sammen "
"med."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:752
#, no-c-format
msgid "Moving speed"
msgstr "Flyttehastighed"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:754
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The more towards <guilabel>Fast</guilabel> the slider is, the faster the "
"floater moves. If the slider is all the way at the <guilabel>Slow</guilabel> "
"end, the floater will stop."
msgstr ""
"Jo længere mod <guilabel>Hurtig</guilabel> skyderen flyttes, desto hurtigere "
"bevæger flyderen sig. Hvis skyderen flyttes så langt som muligt mod "
"<guilabel>Langsom</guilabel>, stopper flyderen."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:760
#, no-c-format
msgid "Signs"
msgstr "Skilte"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:762
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sign HTML:"
msgstr "Underskriv HTML:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:764
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "You can enter any valid &HTML; here. For example, entering <markup>Hit it "
#| "&lt;i&gt;softly&lt;/i&gt; towards the slope!</markup> will create the "
#| "text <quote>Hit it <emphasis>softly</emphasis> towards the slope!</quote>."
msgid ""
"You can enter any valid &HTML; here. For example, entering <userinput>Hit it "
"&lt;i&gt;softly&lt;/i&gt; towards the slope!</userinput> will create the "
"text <quote>Hit it <emphasis>softly</emphasis> towards the slope!</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Du kan indtaste al gyldig &HTML;-kode her. Ved for eksempel at skrive "
"<quote><markup>Slå den &lt;i&gt;forsigtigt&lt;/i&gt; mod hældningen!</"
"markup> </quote> så laves teksten <quote>Slå den <emphasis>forsigtigt</"
"emphasis> mod hældningen!</quote>."

